                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#95r" facs="097">fols. 95r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#102v #103r" facs="105 105">102v, 103r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#11r" facs="013">Fol. 11r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> in a church with an attendant receiving a blessing and the owner of the manuscript taking refuge (on his back before her)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#51r" facs="053">Fol. 51r</locus><desc>Two figures carrying a reclining figure</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#111r" facs="113">Fol. 111r</locus><desc> Reclining cloaked figure. Above the miniature is a prayer to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> <q>“to keep him (the owner of the manuscript?) from <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and arrow.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#125r" facs="127">Fol. 125r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> spearing an enemy</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #6r #12r #18v #26r #31v #42v #51v #58r #62v #73r #83v #86r #90v #95v #105v" facs="003 008 014 021 028 034 045 054 060 065 075 086 088 093 098 108">folss. 1r, 6r, 12r, 18v, 26r, 31v, 42v, 51v, 58r, 62v, 73r, 83v, 86r, 90v, 95v, 105v, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#36r #83v #111v #113r" facs="038 086 114 115">36r, 83v, 111v, 113r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                    <locus target="#112v #114v #116r #118r #119v #120v" facs="115 117 118 120 122 123">112v, 114v, 116r, 118r, 119v, 120v</locus> (line of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
